               <bioghist id="aspace_85bec64e00e867a2e80a1dbca25bb880">
                  <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
                  <p>Sophia Charlotte Howe was the daughter of Richard Howe, Earl Howe and Baron of Langar. As he had no sons, she succeeded him by a provision (a "special remainder") as Baroness Howe of Langar, on August 5, 1799. In 1787 she married Penn Assheton Curzon (1757-1797) of Gopsall Hall in Leicestershire, and in 1812, married Jonathan Wathen Waller (1769-1853).</p>
               </bioghist>
               <scopecontent id="aspace_b9f89e163a94b4a235d01e2036f7221b">
                  <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                  <p>The Baroness sent two dozen lengthy letters from her homes Penn House, Gopsall Hall, and Little Strawberry Hill and Cross Deep in Twickenham, as well as from Weymouth in Dorset, where she spent time with the royal family in residence at the time. Howe was continuously renovating her properties so wrote often of her acquisitions, ongoing projects, and achievements. She generally addressed Mordaunt as "My Dear Sir" but occasionally as "My Dear Cousin."</p>
               </scopecontent>
               <arrangement id="aspace_eba8978d76e81d4af92580b9add46554">
                  <head>Arrangement</head>
